- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Gröbner bases, which is a fundamental concept in symbolic computation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with differential algebra, which is a key tool in systems and control theory. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is another possibility as the paper deals with differential equations and their solutions. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is less likely but still possible as Gröbner bases have connections to logic and automated reasoning. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also less likely but possible as tropical geometry has connections to computational geometry.
